main event: The report details seven incidents of unidentified flying objects sighted in the continental U.S. during March 1950.
interesting points: The location of the sightings was St Johns, Michigan.
The report was sourced from the Intelligence Division, Hq MATS, Andrews AFB, Washington 25, D.C.
The conclusion of the report was 'Insufficient Data'.
There were no photographs or physical evidence linked to the sightings.
The type of observation was categorized as air-visual.
